				 Girls fry egg throwers
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, Oct. 4: Three girls from St Xaviers College dragged three youths by their collars and handed them over to a traffic sergeant for passing lewd remarks and throwing eggs on them near the Rashbehari crossing this evening.																								Police said the girls  all three are mass communication students  were walking down the road after getting off a bus when the youths, identified as Irfan, Nesar and Imranul, began harassing them. 																								The youths were standing at a roadside fast-food outlet. The girls ignored them initially and walked towards a nearby autorickshaw stand. Suddenly, the youths picked up three eggs from the fast-food outlet and hurled them at the girls, said an officer of Kalighat police station.																								The girls  one of them is the daughter of Trinamul Congress councillor Firhad Hakim  marched to the outlet and caught hold of their tormentors. A crowd that had gathered at the scene called a traffic sergeant and the girls took the youths to him. The three were arrested.																								The girls handled the situation boldly and taught them a lesson. They even went to the Kalighat police station to lodge a formal complaint, Hakim said.																								Hostel protest																								Nearly 100 students and boarders of Hindu Hostel staged a road block on the Central Avenue and Zakaria Street crossing tonight in protest against lack of water and electricity for the past 16 hours. 
